<br>
My comments also assume you have a mostly mid 50s raid force of 24 people, with some key higher level classes, such as a tank, clerc, and chanter / shaman.  The 3 day comment from your guildies would be appropriate if you were attempting to go to mage isle (7th) and also were intending on farming the spiroc lord for warriors before heading up.  A good way to plan on doing the raid if commiting large chunks of time is a problem would be to clear to pegasus isle ( might as well clear it too for a chance at the ranger cloak quest piece and necro epic piece if you have any on the raid) then come back the next day / evening and farm the spiroc lord.  That should keep the first day to a 3-4 hour raid, and the 2nd for however long your guild feels it needs to stay there to farm epic pieces.<br>
